About Me
For the past 10 years, I have been in the corporate yoga space where I dedicated myself to developing leaders. As a kid and young adult, I felt like I was never good enough. In my career with yoga, I knew I wanted to make each individual I interacted with knowing they were 1000% enough. When you make space for people that way, they are more likely to multiply that same energy into the world.
I used to be a professional dancer and I was constantly being judged. I had challenges with family relationships, and one day I moved across the country to figure out who I truly was and what my purpose was in life. Yoga found me, I found yoga, and the connection between breath, movement, and heart unlocked something inside me I wanted to share with the world. Since then I married the love of my life and high school sweetheart. We are blessed with a fierce and confident 2 year old daughter, and another baby on the way. I left the corporate yoga space and after my daughter was born I was so fulfilled taking the role of “mom”. When my daughter was about 4 months old, I remember watching one of my all-time favorite television shows “Parenthood” and had this feeling of how do I continue to choose me? I was in the routine of being a wife, mom, daughter, and sister, and I was still missing something. I started looking at master's degrees in psychology and coaching programs. It came down to coaching because asking questions and identifying people's strengths has always been something I have loved. After a 105-degree sweaty and inspirational yoga class, I was the teacher waiting for students to ask them questions about the lessons they wanted to take off the yoga mat. So 5 months into motherhood I said yes to a 9 month coach training program!
I always thought I would be the CEO of a corporation and become a mom with a large family. Can I say this happened? Sort of! It’s a work in progress, and I drive this dream. I founded this coaching business, and adore being a mom. Seeing my daughter explore daily has opened a side of me that reminds me of how I choose myself. As our family expands and as my coaching business develops, they have one thing in common…. Positive Energy!

Choose you for a fulfilling and thriving life!

My name is Christie Cianciulli and I am the founder of Choose You Coaching.

As a positivity coach, I specialize in helping individuals navigate life transitions and achieve personal growth. Whether you're a dedicated mother, embarking on a new career path, or striving for personal development, I am here to be your partner and guide you toward impactful change.
